Eight men accused of gang-raping a thirteen year old in Nyanga will be spending Christmas behind bars as the case was postponed to January 18 2017 for bail application.The accused aged between 18 and 20 years-old made a brief appearance in the Wynberg magistrates court on Tuesday.It is alleged that the girl was abducted at gunpoint while walking alone on Robert Sobukwe Road in Novermber and allegedly taken to a shack where she was repeatedly raped by the accused.Joan van Niekerk of the International Society for the Prevention of Child Abuse and Neglect said that the girl and her relatives will require extensive professional support following her rape.During their previous appearance, the court heard that the girl was raped by 10 men.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter